description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for registered nurses to join our well-established in-patient physical rehabilitation unit based in Billericay.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The unit provides 22 in-patient beds that support facilitation of early discharge from hospital and prevention of admission, by enabling people to regain their independence and realise their full potential in this community setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role incorporates the provision of rehabilitation programs, at the same time you will be responsible for undertaking patient assessment, provision of nursing care and appropriate nursing evaluation. You will also be responsible for assisting the multidiciplinary team working within the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are therefore looking for experienced registered nurses with excellent communication skills, flexibility and evidence of multidisciplinary working. Community and rehabilitation experience will be an advantage but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EPUT are looking for motivated staff who shares our Trust values of Open, Compassionate and Empowering. In return, EPUT can offer you a range of benefits and development including;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name margaret Dias Job title management Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01277 634711&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward Manager - Wendy Gore - 01277634711&lt;/p&gt;
